{"word":"κομιδῇ","slug":"κομιδῇ","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κομιδῇ</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:dative'>dat.</a> of <a href='S:κομιδή'><el>κομιδή</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>exactly, just</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>like <el>πάνυ</el>, <i>absolutely, altogether, quite</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>; <el>οὐ κομιδῇ</el> not <i>at all</i>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b>in answers, <el>κομιδῇ μὲν οὖν</el> <i>just so</i>, yes <i>certainly</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}